Hi, Viorel :) Sorry for the delay in replying. Overall, everything is fine here. We all caught a little cold, but nothing serious. In October my wife will have an operation and will need to stay in the hospital for about a week.  At the moment I don‚Äôt really know what to focus on ‚Äî there are no concrete plans. Earlier we had the move to prepare for, but now there‚Äôs nothing visible on the horizon. We also don‚Äôt have any vacation plans for now, but our child was really impressed by the mountains in Switzerland. Recently we‚Äôve been watching a lot about mountain expeditions and climbs. I could imagine planning something like a hike or even dreaming about Everest one day, but for now a proper hiking trip would already be great. Of course, at this age our child wouldn‚Äôt handle altitude sickness, so Everest has to wait.  Bernhard told me about the big plant opening and the celebration ‚Äî congratulations on that, it sounds like a great event!  And how are things on your side? What are you focusing on these days?
Hi Dima,¬† ¬† I did not hear from you for a long time. Are you ok?¬† Regards,¬† Viorel

Hi Dima,¬† I was in a longer holiday and came back this week. Not surprisingly, there is no answer from them regarding my contact request. I have no choice but to maintain my opinion that your tribe is very peculiar.¬† I am beginning to think that this road leads to nowhere. Perhaps we need a new approach here.¬† ¬† Just purely theoretical, if everything could be made possible, would you be able to consider a direct employment by Josera Germany or Poland? ¬† Otherwise, how are you, your wife and son? I hope that by now the wounds from the teeth extraction in your wife's case have healed well.¬†üôÇ ¬†Are there vacation plans?

Thank you for the kind words.¬†  And yeah, that‚Äôs exactly what I meant ‚Äî thanks for checking the link! The company does seem strange from the outside. No replies, no signals‚Ä¶ Here, sometimes I just want a simple routine task for a day or two ‚Äî to relax and stop doing what and where I have lack of knowledge or experience.  I‚Äôve recently had a taste of being a coordinator myself ‚Äî and honestly, I don‚Äôt know how you manage it long term. It‚Äôs exhausting. Total respect!

Hi Dima,¬† I cannot say I envy your wife. I got all my wisdom teeth pulled out in one single operation. I know what she is going through. :).¬† Yes, for kids there are sealing treatments and we have done it for the older daughter. The doctor said we had to wait for the teeth in the back to fully come out so that they are also treated. That did not happen yet by the younger daughter.¬† ¬† I wish your wife success in finding the job that she would like to have.¬† Here we have warmth, it is nice to go out and walk in the woods. No working though. Woods is just for fun.¬† ¬† Thank you for the link. I must say, the company you work at is a little bit strange. No one answers at the telephone, no answers to the Linked-In inquiries in Belarus or even in Germany..... ¬†Are you sure you are allright there? Or do they keep you prisoner, tied to the working desk? :)

Thanks a lot for your message! About Belarus ‚Äî when we arrived, we focused more on health. In Lithuania, medical services were not very accessible, and doctors often had only surface-level knowledge. If you really want to solve something, it costs a fortune. I guess all the smartest doctors already moved to Germany anyway! üòÑ  My wife has a wisdom tooth deep in the jaw, she‚Äôll have surgery. I also went for a check, now they do 3D scans and find EXTRA ‚Äúopportunities‚Äù to fix ‚Äî for a price, of course.  I heard that for kids (6‚Äì10 years) they can do some kind of ‚Äúseal‚Äù treatment on the teeth (dental sealants) to help prevent cavities later. Did you do this for your kids?  The wife is still without a job. In the place she wanted, nothing worked out. We have friends who run a language school, so she might help there a bit. In the ideal world, she‚Äôd start her own project, but now it‚Äôs easier to go bankrupt than succeed.  Again, honestly, I haven‚Äôt seen much real interest from them.¬† You can at least submit a request here so they contact you directly: https://www.epam.com/services/partners/sap#contact  How are things on your side? Now is probably the best weather to work in the forest ‚Äî I remember you mentioned you live close to it. I don‚Äôt have a forest nearby, so I just stare at buildings from my window.

Hi Dima, I was away for a few days and not checked my account.  ¬† Indeed we have some areas (SD, TM-FI) where your replacement is more or less clueless and that does not help.¬† ¬† But it is not only about the unfinished work. We really enjoyed working with you, having you around. :) ¬† I propose that you let me help you. I would need a contact from the sales department. Normally they never refuse money :).¬† How is the family? Did you all manage to adapt to the new life in Belarus? I suspect that for your son it was very good to be able to see his grandparents.
To be honest, I still feel a bit guilty ‚Äî some of the work dragged on and I didn‚Äôt manage to wrap everything up properly before leaving
I‚Äôll still talk to another manager (there are many here), but honestly, I wouldn‚Äôt count on it

Hi, Viorel, how are you doing?   I guess it's that time soon when you work from the forest with your laptop ‚Äî must be nice to live so close to nature.  I checked on my side ‚Äî a bit unexpected for me too, but the company wants me to focus solely on the their project. They don‚Äôt really support side work, even with a new client. So they weren‚Äôt really interested in going forward with that.  I‚Äôd be glad to keep in touch now and then ‚Äî I really liked working with you

Hi Dima,¬† ¬† you know, we are always busy with things. But we are missing you :). I cannot believe that there is already a month since you left. If feels like yesterday we spoke about the split valuation... ¬† Bernhard is also asking about how you are doing. I hope you will settle in very good and that you will soon start enjoying the life in your country, with your family. And the dog will forget the nightmare of moving with the car with some Josera treats.¬†üòÅ.¬† With the warmest regards,¬† Viorel

Hi Viorel, Thank you for your message ‚Äî it means a lot!¬†  To be honest, since coming back I‚Äôve been a bit out of reality. Even though a few weeks have passed, I still don‚Äôt feel fully settled in ‚Äî neither at home nor at work. The move was intense: just 180 km, but it took us 11 hours! The worst part? Our dog ‚Äî she absolutely hates being in the car, poor pet üòÖ  As for your question ‚Äî I‚Äôll bring it up with the manager and get back to you as soon as I get any meaningful response.¬†  And how are you doing, Viorel? I hope things are going well on your side. Right?

Hi Dima, I hope you have integrated well in you new work environment and in you home land.¬† ¬†Now that you are inside the new company, can you please name someone from sales, with whom I may take contact?¬† You know, we did not forget you :) Thank you and have a very nice weekend! Viorel

CONTENT: Dear Dzmitryi,  Please let me know if you OR if you know someone who is currently looking, is interested in the following SAP job offer (please reply even if this is not of interest, so that I get my InMail credit refunded :-) )  SAP SD Consultant - English speaking - 100% Remote from NL. Permanent Job. Start Q1 / Q2 2025. Salary: up to ‚Ç¨130,000/annum plus benefits.  Our end client in the Netherlands is looking for an SAP SD (Sales & Distribution) Consultant to lead SAP SD Projects across EMEA (working 100% remotely). The role reports into the Senior Director of IT, and is responsible for coordinating and serving as the Functional Authority for SAP enhancement projects and for designing effective business-oriented SAP solutions.  Role Requirements: * 5 years+ SAP SD experience on either SAP ECC or SAP S/4HANA. * Developing and presenting technical documentation and training materials. * Experience with troubleshooting and remedying complex production issues with SAP SD. * Experience of booking program creation and support. * Effectively lead cross-functional, multi-national teams through complex information technology projects. * A willingness to learn SAP EWM and SAP FI.  Responsibilities: * Providing SAP functional guidance to professional and technical staff. * Analyzing and evaluating business requirements. * Consulting with various departments to identify business processes to automate and/or improve. * Guiding strategic plans for systems/applications development. * Acting as technical lead over business improvement projects. Hi, my name is Ilya, I‚Äôm from Alconost.I'm looking for outstanding people to join my Sales team.At Alconost we localize software, mobile apps, games, and websites into more than seventy languages. Our translators are native speakers living in a number of different countries. Our clients are companies that create and sell software, websites, and games. They include Fortune 500 businesses alongside small indie companies.Alconost has been demonstrating sustainable growth during the past 15 years. That growth is supported by our Sales Team, which includes both Outbound and Inbound Sales Managers.The person I'm looking for will work with our Outbound sales team to help us continue to grow our services. As a rule, this will be a university graduate who is pleasant to deal with, who speaks English fluently and has the ability to conduct business correspondence in it, and preferably knows a second‚Äîand sometimes a third‚Äîforeign language. They will be polite and proactive at the same time, open-minded and goal-oriented, and not afraid to take responsibility. We are looking for someone who truly loves making connections, talking to people and writing inspiring letters, and who won‚Äôt be demotivated after hearing ‚ÄúNo thanks‚Äù a hundred times or when they don‚Äôt get an answer after the hundredth follow-up.Ideally, they will have experience in international Sales or Business development, and will be ready (and know what to do) to start selling from day one.Since we work with software developers, a Sales Manager‚Äôs background is quite important. It‚Äôs great if they are interested in IT, have a general understanding of how product and service companies work and make money, what the product development cycle looks like, and how apps or games are built and sold in general. It‚Äôs also great if they know how to put an HTML page together, and understand what XML and JSON are.That‚Äôs the kind of person we‚Äôre looking for right now: either someone who is already an experienced professional, or someone prepared to learn everything with our help.If you have previous experience in international Sales, or if you studied technical subjects at university, but have a passion for foreign languages, or if you‚Äôre a linguist, but you dream of working in IT,‚Äîthen the job of Sales Manager may well be for you.About companyAlconost is a kind of startup with a more than ten-year history of continuous growth and development. Unlike a classic startup, we are in no hurry. We are looking for ‚ÄúHackers‚Äù - people who achieve results at any cost, who bring the case to the end, who are not afraid to take full responsibility, who are constantly looking for alternative opportunities where it seems impossible.At Alconost we believe in a work-life balance. There‚Äôs a lot of serious work, but the timetable is flexible, and a Sales Manager is someone who knows how to manage their own workload. That does mean you‚Äôll often need to be contactable on weekends and public holidays, but on the other hand you'll get plenty of time to attend to your own business during working days. The main thing is to get the priorities right and not to become a bottleneck in your clients‚Äô business.You will not be bound by strict KPIs, but at the same time your compensation will be fully dependent on your performance.We mostly work remotely. Initially you‚Äôll need to come into the office for training, but after that you can work from anywhere on the planet.Please visit our website to learn more about us: https://alconost.comIf you‚Äôre interested in this opening, please apply below.
